" █▀░ █ █▄▄ ██▄   ░█░ ░█░ █▀▀ ██▄ ▄█   █▀█ ▄█ ▄█ █▄█ █▄▄ █ █▀█ ░█░ █ █▄█ █░▀█
" @association

"  GIT
fileviewer {.git/}, git -c color.status=always status %d %pu

"  DIRECTORY PREVIEW
fileviewer {*/,.*/,../},
      \ lsd --almost-all --color=always --icon=always --group-directories-first --blocks=permission --blocks=name,
      \ lsd --almost-all --color=always --icon=always --group-directories-first --tree --depth=3,
      \ df -h %f | highlight -O ansi --syntax javascript,
      \ ls --color=always

"  DATABASE
filextype {*.db,*.sqlite3},
      \ {View with DB Browser}
      \ sqlitebrowser --read-only %c,
      \ {Edit with DB Browser}
      \ sqlitebrowser %c

fileviewer {*.db,*.sqlite3},
      \ sqlite3 %f "SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table';",
      \ stat %f,
      \ sqlite3 %f ".schema",

"  CSV
fileviewer *.csv,
      \ cat %c | xsv table,
      \ sed "s/,,,,/,,-,,/g;s/,,/ /g" %c | column -t | sed "s/ - /  /g" | cut -c -%pw

"  PDF
filextype {*.pdf},<application/pdf>
      \ {View in zathura}
      \ zathura %c %i,
      \ {View with mupdf}
      \ mupdf %c,
      \ {View with apvlv}
      \ apvlv %c,
      \ {View with qpdfview}
      \ qpdfview %c,
      \ {View with xpdf}
      \ xpdf %c
fileviewer {*.pdf},<application/pdf>
      " Text reading order
      \ pdftotext -nopgbrk %c -,
      " Text content stream order
      \ pdftotext -raw -nopgbrk %c -,
      " Maintains columns, hyphenation etc.
      \ pdftotext -nopgbrk -layout %c -,
      \ pdfinfo %c,

"  AUDIO
filetype {*.wav,*.mp3,*.flac,*.m4a,*.wma,*.ac3,*.og[agx],*.opus,*.aac,*.mpga},<audio/*>
      \ {Play using mpv}
      \ mpv --no-video %f %s,
      \ {Play using ffplay}
      \ ffplay -nodisp -hide_banner -autoexit %c,
      \ {Play using MPlayer}
      \ mplayer %f,
fileviewer {*.wav,*.mp3,*.flac,*.m4a,*.wma,*.ac3,*.og[agx],*.opus,*.aac,*.mpga},<audio/*>
      \ ffprobe -hide_banner -pretty %c 2>&1

"  IMAGES
filextype {*.svg,*.svgz},<image/svg+xml>
      \ {View in feh}
      \ feh --start-at %d/%c:r.%c:e --scale-down --draw-tinted,
      \ {Edit in Inkscape}
      \ inkscape %f,
      \ {View in Inkview}
      \ inkview %f,
      \ {Edit in NeoVim}
      \ nvim %f,
filextype {*.cr2}
      \ {Open in Darktable}
      \ darktable %f,
      \ {Open in RawTherapee}
      \ rawtherapee %f,
filextype {*.xcf}
      \ {Open in GIMP}
      \ gimp %f,
filextype {.kra}
      \ {Open in Krita}
      \ krita %f,
filextype {.blend}
      \ {Open in Blender}
      \ blender %c,
filextype {*.gif}
      \ {Play using mpv}
      \ mpv --terminal=no %f,
filextype {*.bmp,*.jpg,*.jpeg,*.png,*.xpm},<image/*>
      \ {View in feh}
      \ feh --start-at %d/%c:r.%c:e --scale-down --draw-tinted --version-sort --sort=name,
      \ {Slideshow in feh}
      \ feh --start-at %d/%c:r.%c:e --scale-down --draw-tinted --version-sort --sort=name --slideshow-delay=3,
      \ {View in nomacs}
      \ nomacs %f -m 'frameless',
      \ {Set as Wallpaper with SWWW}
      \ swww img %f -t 'center',
      \ {Edit in NeoVim}
      \ nvim %f,
fileviewer {*.bmp,*.jpg,*.jpeg,*.png,*.gif,*.xpm},<image/*>
      \ exiv2 %f 2> /dev/null | highlight -O ansi --syntax conf,
      \ exiv2 -PEkt %f 2> /dev/null | highlight -O ansi --syntax conf,
      \ kitten icat --silent --transfer-mode=file --place=%pwx%ph@%pxx%py %c >/dev/tty </dev/tty %N
      \ %pc
      \ kitten icat --clear --silent >/dev/tty </dev/tty %N

"  VIDEO
filextype {*.avi,*.mp4,*.wmv,*.dat,*.3gp,*.ogv,*.mkv,*.mpg,*.mpeg,*.vob,
      \*.fl[icv],*.m2v,*.mov,*.webm,*.mts,*.m4v,*.r[am],*.qt,*.divx,
      \*.as[fx],*.unknown_video},<video/*>
      \ {Play using mpv GPU}
      \ mpv --terminal=no %f,
      \ {     |---- mpv TTY Terminal}
      \ mpv --vo=tct %f,
      \ {     |---- mpv Kitty Protocol}
      \ mpv --vo=kitty %f,
      \ {View using ffplay}
      \ ffplay -fs -hide_banner -autoexit %f,
      \ {View using Dragon}
      \ dragon %f:p,
      \ {View using mplayer}
      \ mplayer %f,
fileviewer {*.avi,*.mp4,*.wmv,*.dat,*.3gp,*.ogv,*.mkv,*.mpg,*.mpeg,*.vob,
      \*.fl[icv],*.m2v,*.mov,*.webm,*.mts,*.m4v,*.r[am],*.qt,*.divx,
      \*.as[fx],*.unknown_video},<video/*>
      \ $VIFM/scripts/ffprobe.sh %c,
      \ ffprobe -hide_banner -v error -pretty -print_format json -show_private_data -show_format -show_streams  %c | highlight -O ansi --syntax json,
      \ ffprobe -hide_banner -pretty %c 2>&1 | highlight -O ansi --syntax ini

"  OFFICE FILES
filextype { *.odt,*.doc,*.docx,*.odp,*.pptx,*.ppt},
      \ <application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.*,
      \ application/msword,
      \ application/vnd.ms-excel>
      \ libreoffice %f & disown
fileviewer {*.doc},<application/msword> catdoc %c
fileviewer {*.odt},
      \ odt2txt %f -
fileviewer {*.docx},
      \<application/
      \vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document>
      \ docx2txt %f -

"  SPREADSHEET FILES
filextype {*.ods,*.xls,*.xlsx},
      \ {Open in Libre Office}
      \ libreoffice --calc %f & disown,

"  WEB
filextype {*.xhtml,*.html,*.htm},<text/html>
      \ {Open with firefox}
      \ firefox %f &,
      \ {Open with qutebrowser}
      \ qutebrowser %f %i,
filetype {*.xhtml,*.html,*.htm},<text/html> links, lynx

"  FUSE ZIP MOUNT
filetype {*.zip,*.jar,*.war,*.ear,*.oxt,*.apkg},
      \<application/zip,application/java-archive>
      \ {Mount with fuse-zip}
      \ FUSE_MOUNT|fuse-zip %SOURCE_FILE %DESTINATION_DIR,
      \ {7Zip - Extract}
      \ 7z e %c -o%d/%c:r,
      \ {unzip - Extract}
      \ unzip %c -d %d/%c:r,
      \ {unzip - Test Integrity}
      \ unzip -tq %c,
      \ {View contents}
      \ unzip -l %f | less,
      \ {Open with 7Zip-GUI}
      \ 7zFM %d/%c,
fileviewer *.zip,*.jar,*.war,*.ear,*.oxt unzip -l %f

" LaTeX
filetype *.tex
      \ {Edit in nvim}
      \ nvim %f,
      \ {Convert to PDF with pdflatex (clean)}
      \ sh -c 'pdflatex %f && rm -f %c:r.aux %c:r.log %c:r.out %c:r.toc',

